.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:31:# Feature Specification: Deep research (MiniMax M2.7) on how to implement the deep-agent-improvement model-benchmark mode
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:50:| **Successor** | 003-build-benchmark-mode |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:60:The 001 design names the mode-selector approach + three seams at the ADR level, but the build packet needs sharper implementation detail: exact interface contracts for each seam, how to generalize `dispatch-minimax.cjs` into a model-agnostic `dispatch-model.cjs`, how to port the 120/003 eval-rig scorer cleanly, and how to wire `mode` into `loop.cjs` without regressing the agent-improvement path. This also dogfoods MiniMax M2.7 as a deep-research executor.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:73:- Questions: per-seam interface contracts (candidate-source / dispatcher / scorer); `dispatch-minimax.cjs` → `dispatch-model.cjs` generalization; porting the eval-rig scorer + rubric; `mode` wiring in `loop.cjs`; backward-compat test strategy; implementation edge cases/pitfalls
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:123:| Dependency | MiniMax M2.7 via cli-opencode | High — no run without it | Confirmed live (`opencode models minimax`); `--pure` keeps Write/Bash tools |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:124:| Risk | MiniMax (smaller model) unreliable at the 3-artifact output contract | High | Probe iteration 1 first; loop has 3-failure→stuck-recovery + resumable state; surface (don't silently switch) if it can't hold |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:134:- RESOLVED: The research added real implementation depth beyond 001's ADRs — notably the no-`loop.cjs` / journal-based discovery and the new `loop-host.cjs` entry point, plus concrete seam contracts and a build-delta.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:145:- **Key discovery**: deep-agent-improvement has **no `loop.cjs`** (journal-based orchestration). The mode switch needs a new `loop-host.cjs` entry point; `reduce-state.cjs` needs no structural change (mode metadata only).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:146:- **Dispatcher**: `dispatch-model.cjs` generalizes `dispatch-minimax.cjs` via an executor-routing map; `modelBenchmarkConfig` lives in `improvement_config.json`; absent/`agent-improvement` mode never loads it (backward-compat).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md:149:- **Build delta**: CREATE `loop-host.cjs`, `dispatch-model.cjs`, grader factory; MODIFY `score-candidate.cjs`, `run-benchmark.cjs`, `promote-candidate.cjs`, `reduce-state.cjs`.
