.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:60:This is **Phase 8** of the two-lane program. The deep-agent-improvement skill already has two runtime lanes: Lane A (agent-improvement, improve an agent `.md` file) and Lane B (model-benchmark, benchmark or optimize a model or prompt framework). Lane B works as a skill mode but has no command entry. This phase makes Lane B first-class at the command layer.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:62:**Scope Boundary**: Command-layer surfaces only (command markdown, command YAML assets, gemini mirror, README, advisor routing). No change to the loop-host or benchmark runtime, which already support `--mode=model-benchmark` (verified in phases 003 to 005).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:65:- The model-benchmark runtime contract from phases 003 to 005 (`loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark`, fixtures, scorers, mode-aware promotion). This phase consumes it, it does not change it.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:66:- The existing Lane A command and its two YAML assets, used as the template for the Lane B equivalents.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:69:- A use-case lane question added to the agent-improvement command so it can branch to the model-benchmark workflow.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:70:- Two Lane B workflow YAMLs (`_auto` and `_confirm`).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:71:- A dedicated `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command plus its gemini mirror.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:84:The model-benchmark lane of deep-agent-improvement runs end-to-end at the runtime layer (`loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark`) but has no command entry, so a user cannot start a benchmark run without hand-writing the loop-host invocation. The existing `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command also never asks which use-case lane the user wants, so it silently assumes agent-improvement and the benchmark lane stays invisible. The result is a capability that exists in the skill but is unreachable through the normal command surface.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:87:Make the model-benchmark lane first-class at the command layer: the agent-improvement command asks the use-case lane and branches, and a dedicated `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command starts benchmark runs directly, both backed by Lane B workflow YAMLs and registered in the README and the advisor.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:97:- Create the two Lane B workflow YAMLs (`deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_auto.yaml`, `deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_confirm.yaml`) that drive the model-benchmark runtime contract.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:98:- Create the dedicated `start-model-benchmark-loop.md` command and its gemini mirror `start-model-benchmark-loop.toml`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:102:- Changing the loop-host or benchmark runtime (fixtures, scorers, grader, promotion) - that contract shipped in phases 003 to 005 and is reused as-is.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:110:| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_auto.yaml` | Create | Lane B auto-mode workflow YAML |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:111:| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_confirm.yaml` | Create | Lane B confirm-mode workflow YAML |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:112:| `.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md` | Create | Dedicated Lane B command |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:113:| `.gemini/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.toml` | Create | Gemini mirror of the Lane B command |
