.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/graph-metadata.json:177:        "name": "Two Lane",
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/graph-metadata.json:207:    "causal_summary": "This is **Phase 8** of the two-lane program. The deep-agent-improvement skill already has two runtime lanes: Lane A (agent-improvement, improve an agent `.md` file) and Lane B (model-benchmark, benchmark or optimize a model or prompt framework). Lane B works as a skill mode but has no command entry. This phase makes Lane B first-class at the command layer.",
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:2:title: "Implementation Summary: Command lane-asking for the model-benchmark lane"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "Phase 008 shipped the two-lane command experience: the agent-improvement command now resolves a use-case lane and a dedicated model-benchmark command plus its workflow YAMLs make Lane B first-class. A latent loop-host arg-forwarding defect was fixed."
