.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/011-agent-lane-note/spec.md:82:The @deep-agent-improvement agent note called the skill "two modes" with model-benchmark as a separate mode bolt-on. That framing under-described the now co-equal Lane B and risked implying Lane B spawns or dispatches a second Claude agent, when in fact Lane B dispatches MODELS via dispatch-model.cjs and there is only ONE agent.
