.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:28:# Decision Record: Design: add a model/prompt-framework benchmark mode to deep-agent-improvement (port the 120/003 rig behind a mode selector)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:31:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr_rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:36:## ADR-001: Add a `mode` selector to deep-agent-improvement (agent-improvement | model-benchmark)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:54:The 120/003 packet proved a model/prompt-framework benchmark loop works (run MiniMax against fixtures under 5 frameworks, score, hill-climb, pick TIDD-EC + dense). But that rig is packet-local and one-off. deep-agent-improvement runs the same loop shape (generate candidate, score, converge, promote) for agent definitions. We needed to decide how to make model benchmarking a reusable capability without duplicating loop infrastructure or distorting the existing agent-improvement skill.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:60:- The two modes score fundamentally different objects (agent-definition quality vs model task-output quality), so their scorers/rubrics cannot be unified.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:69:**We chose**: Add a `mode` config key to deep-agent-improvement with two values, `agent-improvement` (default, today's behavior) and `model-benchmark` (port of the 120/003 rig), dispatched through three pluggable seams.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:71:**How it works**: The loop orchestrator reads `mode` and resolves three seams from it — a **candidate source**, a **dispatcher**, and a **scorer**. The shared plumbing (mutation coverage, state reducer, convergence, journal, fixture materializer) runs identically for both modes. Only the three seams differ.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:75:| Seam | agent-improvement (today) | model-benchmark (new) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:77:| Candidate source | parse `.opencode/agents/*.md` into a scored candidate | render a prompt-framework variant (port `render-variant.cjs` + variant templates from 120/003) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:78:| Dispatcher | none (evaluates local files) | dispatch a model via a CLI (generalize `dispatch-minimax.cjs` → `dispatch-model.cjs` taking executor + model + args, so any cli-X works) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:79:| Scorer | dynamic 5-dim agent rubric (`score-candidate.cjs`) | task-output 5-dim rubric + deterministic checks + grader (port `eval-rig/` + `score-variant.cjs`) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:85:| `mutation-coverage.cjs`, `reduce-state.cjs`, `converge.cjs`, `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs`, `improvement-journal.cjs` | Reuse as-is (already generic; namespaced by loop_type) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:87:| candidate source / dispatcher / scorer | Mode-specific (factory per mode) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:98:| **Mode selector in deep-agent-improvement (chosen)** | ~90% infra reuse; one skill owns "iterative eval loops"; backward compatible | Adds a second mode to a focused skill; needs seam discipline | 8/10 |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:99:| New dedicated skill (e.g. sk-model-benchmark) | Clean separation | Duplicates the loop/state/convergence plumbing; two skills to maintain | 5/10 |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:103:**Why this one**: The two loops are siblings (same shape, different object). A mode selector shares the proven plumbing while keeping the genuinely-different parts (scorer, dispatch, promotion) cleanly separate, and it is non-breaking for existing agent-improvement runs.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:112:- Model/prompt benchmarking becomes a repeatable command instead of a hand-ported rig.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:113:- ~90% of the loop infra is shared, so the new mode is mostly seams + a ported scorer, not a second engine.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:116:- A second mode in a previously single-purpose skill. Mitigation: strict seam interfaces + a `mode` default that preserves current behavior.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:123:| Seam abstraction leaks; modes entangle | M | Interface contracts + seam tests; scorers/promotion stay separate |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:134:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | We just hand-ported the rig for 120/003; the next model benchmark would repeat that. |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:135:| 2 | **Beyond Local Maxima?** | PASS | 4 options compared (mode selector, new skill, deep-loop-runtime, status quo). |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:136:| 3 | **Sufficient?** | PASS | Mode selector + 3 seams is the minimum that reuses the plumbing without unifying the incompatible scorers. |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:137:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | Directly answers the user's ask: deep-agent-improvement should also benchmark models. |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:138:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Generalized `dispatch-model.cjs` supports any cli-X model, not just MiniMax. |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:149:- deep-agent-improvement SKILL.md + `improvement_config.json` gain the `mode` selector.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:150:- New `dispatch-model.cjs` + ported `eval-rig/` + `score-variant.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:159:## ADR-002: deep-agent-improvement is the home (not a new skill, not deep-loop-runtime)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:163:**Decision**: House the model-benchmark mode inside deep-agent-improvement. deep-loop-runtime was rejected because it is a read-only shared library (executor/prompt-pack/scorer helpers consumed by deep-review/research), not a loop orchestrator with mutation + promotion. A new dedicated skill was rejected because it would duplicate the loop/state/convergence plumbing deep-agent-improvement already owns. deep-agent-improvement already has the mutation-coverage, reducer, convergence, journal, and benchmark-fixture machinery, so it is the lowest-duplication home.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:165:**Consequence**: deep-agent-improvement's identity broadens from "agent improvement" to "iterative evaluation loops (agent improvement + model benchmarking)". Its SKILL.md description + triggers update accordingly in the build.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:167:## ADR-003: Keep scorers, fixtures, and promotion mode-separate
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:171:**Decision**: Share only the proven-generic plumbing; keep the scorer (agent 5-dim rubric vs task-output 5-dim rubric + grader), the fixture adapter (agent fixtures vs task fixtures), and promotion (agent file-copy + mirror-sync vs synthesis-only) as mode-specific implementations. Do not attempt a unified rubric — the two modes score fundamentally different objects, and forcing one rubric would be a wrong abstraction.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:178:HVR rules: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr_rules.md
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:3:description: "Architecture decisions and per-finding disposition register for remediating the 014 two-lane deep review: space-form parser, read-only grader sandbox, fixture-id sanitization, criteria-exec fail-closed default, packet-local candidate-keyed cache."
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:7:  - "Lane B parser decision"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:12:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:32:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr_rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:52:The 014 review confirmed F-P0-1: `loop-host.cjs` `parseArgs` only accepts `--key=value` and bare flags, but all three Lane B command surfaces invoke loop-host with SPACE-form flags (`--profile {profile} --scorer {scoring_method} --grader {grader}`), so `profile`, `outputs-dir`, `scorer`, and `grader` all parse to `true`. The model-benchmark command does not run as intended. We could either teach the parser the space-form or rewrite the three command surfaces to `=`-form.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:56:- TST-1 byte-identity gate must hold: the `=`-form parse path and the Lane A plan must be byte-identical pre and post fix.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:89:- The Lane B command runs as intended through the YAML path.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:110:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | P0 release blocker; Lane B is broken without it |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:125:- `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs` `parseArgs`: additive space-form branch.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:126:- `scripts/tests/loop-host.vitest.ts`: space-form test + TST-1 identity assertion.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:150:F-P1-1 found `buildSpawnSpec` runs external model executors with write-capable modes (Claude `--permission-mode acceptEdits`, Codex `--sandbox workspace-write`, Devin `--permission-mode auto`). Grading and benchmarking should observe output, not edit the workspace.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:163:**We chose**: Default grader/executor dispatch to read-only/no-edit modes, with an explicit documented opt-in for write-capable evaluation in an isolated temp workspace, and assert `cwd` stays inside the benchmark sandbox before spawning.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:165:**How it works**: `buildSpawnSpec` emits read-only permission flags per executor by default. A documented opt-in flag or env var switches to write-capable mode only when the caller explicitly requests it, and the spawn path validates the resolved `cwd` is inside the benchmark sandbox first.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:222:- `scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs` `buildSpawnSpec`: read-only default + cwd sandbox assert + opt-in.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:247:F-P1-9 found fixture-controlled `fixture.id` is used in `path.join(outputsDir, ` + "`${fixture.id}.md`" + `)` without validating it is a basename or that the resolved path stays under `outputsDir`. A crafted id with separators or `..` can read or score files outside the benchmark output directory.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:262:**How it works**: A small guard validates the id is a single safe basename, the runner resolves `outputsDir` and the candidate path, and asserts containment via a separator-bounded prefix check before any file access.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:284:- Fixture ids cannot escape the benchmark output directory.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:318:- `scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs`: fixture-id guard + resolved-inside-outputs assert.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:347:- Existing trusted benchmark profiles may rely on criteria execution and must remain reachable via explicit opt-in.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:424:## ADR-005: Move the score cache packet-local and key it by candidate
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:439:Two findings target the score cache. F-P1-11: `defaultCacheDir()` stores scores under `os.tmpdir()/deep-agent-improvement-score-cache`, a shared world-writable path that is later trusted before rescoring. F-P1-12: the cache input hash includes candidate content and target path but not `candidatePath` or `baselinePath`, so a cache hit can carry the wrong candidate or baseline path in the result payload.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:444:- Cache hits must not mislabel which candidate or baseline produced the score.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:452:**We chose**: Store the cache packet-local (under the runtime/packet root) with owner/mode validation, treat unreadable or untrusted entries as cache misses, and include `candidatePath` and `baselinePath` in the cache key.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:454:**How it works**: `defaultCacheDir()` resolves under the packet/runtime root with restrictive permissions; reads validate owner and mode and fall back to a miss on mismatch. The cache key hash adds the candidate and baseline paths, so a hit always corresponds to the exact candidate it scored.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:464:| **Packet-local + candidate-keyed (chosen)** | Closes the trust gap and the mislabel gap together | Cache no longer shared across packets | 9/10 |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:477:- A cache hit always names the correct candidate and baseline.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:511:- `scripts/agent-improvement/score-candidate.cjs`: packet-local cache dir + owner/mode validation; cache key includes candidate and baseline paths.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:527:| F-P0-1 | P0 | Lane B command flags misparse to booleans | FIXED | ADR-001; space-form parseArgs + test + e2e |
