.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:181:| NFR-003 | Traceability | Failure reports and ledger rows carry scorer, grader, and profile provenance |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:182:| NFR-004 | Packet-local state | Score cache, pause sentinel, and benchmark reports live under the packet/runtime root, not a shared path |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:189:- `=`-form flag with an empty value (`--scorer=`): preserved as today (byte-identical).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:192:- `record.mode` missing or misspelled: bucketed as unknown or warned, not silently counted as Lane A.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:198:Level 3. The packet touches multiple lane-separated scripts, two Lane B YAMLs, several command and agent docs, and the advisor scorer, across security, traceability, and maintainability dimensions. The risk concentration is the P0 parser change (TST-1 byte-identity must hold) and the security cluster (each fix needs an adversarial or regression test). The change set is broad but each fix is surgical and file-scoped.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:215:- As a benchmark operator, I run `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` and the profile, outputs-dir, scorer, and grader flags take effect, so the run benchmarks what I asked for.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:217:- As an auditor, I read a failure report and ledger row that name the scorer, grader, and profile, so I can tell a failed 5dim/llm run from a pattern/noop run.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/spec.md:222:- Should the score cache live packet-local keyed by candidate, or stay in a shared tmp path? Chosen: packet-local plus candidate-keyed (see decision-record ADR-005).
