.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:17:### F1 — deep-agent-improvement has no `loop.cjs` — the loop IS the orchestration
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:19:The deep-agent-improvement skill does not have a `loop.cjs`. Its "loop" is the journal-serialized orchestration via:
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:22:- `promote-candidate.cjs` — decides based on scores whether to accept/reject
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:24:The 120/003 `loop.cjs` is a synchronous imperative script that coordinates `dispatch → score → converge → mutate` in a single process. deep-agent-improvement uses a different pattern: async journal appends, separate reducer runs, and explicit promotion gating.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:26:**Implication**: The "mode switch" for deep-agent-improvement must be implemented at the **entry point** that drives the journal-based loop (likely an `index.cjs` or `main.cjs` that doesn't yet exist), NOT inside reduce-state.cjs which is purely reactive.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:30:### F2 — `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` is already standalone and gated
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:32:This script (97 LOC) takes `--profile` and `--outputs-dir` as required args. It does NOT check any mode flag — it simply materializes fixtures when invoked. It is invoked by the benchmark runner (`run-benchmark.cjs`) as part of the benchmark scoring pipeline.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:34:For model-benchmark mode, `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` must be called before `run-benchmark.cjs`. For agent-improvement mode, neither is called. The current calling pattern is:
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:37:run-benchmark.cjs --profile <x> --outputs-dir <y>
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:38:  └── internally calls materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs? NO — they are separate scripts
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:41:Actually, `run-benchmark.cjs` does NOT call `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs`. It loads fixtures directly via `loadFixtures()` (lines 85–93). The materializer is a **separate step** that must be called before `run-benchmark.cjs` to produce the `.md` output files that `scoreFixture()` reads.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:43:**Gating rule**: materialize should ONLY run when mode=`model-benchmark`. In agent-improvement, the benchmark pipeline is not relevant.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:49:`reduce-state.cjs` (1146 LOC) reads `agent-improvement-state.jsonl` and emits `experiment-registry.json` + `agent-improvement-dashboard.md`. It has NO mode awareness. Every record in the state log carries a `type` field that allows it to be bucketed correctly regardless of whether the record came from agent-improvement or model-benchmark scoring.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:52:- `scored` / `accepted` / `rejected` — from score-candidate.cjs (agent-improvement)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:53:- `benchmark_run` — from run-benchmark.cjs (model-benchmark)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:54:- `infra_failure` — from either scorer
