.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/016-script-subfolder-readmes/implementation-summary.md:49:Every source subfolder under `scripts/` now has a code-folder README aligned with the sk-doc code template, so a developer gets local orientation before editing any lane. Nine new READMEs were authored and the four existing ones audited (the root `scripts/README.md` was rewritten from a skill-readme shape onto the code-folder template).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/016-script-subfolder-readmes/implementation-summary.md:53:`agent-improvement/` and `shared/` (the lanes), `model-benchmark/` plus the full scorer subtree (`scorer/`, `scorer/deterministic/`, `scorer/grader/`, `scorer/grader/prompts/`, `scorer/lib/`), and `tests/fixtures/`. Each documents the folder purpose, key files with responsibilities, boundaries, entrypoints, and validation, sized to the folder (small folders carry only overview plus key files). The gitignored runtime `scorer/cache/` dirs are excluded.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/016-script-subfolder-readmes/implementation-summary.md:57:`scripts/README.md` rewritten onto the code-folder template with the post-reorg lane tree; `lib/README.md` gained the missing `trigger_phrases`; `tests/README.md` and `tests/fixtures/low-sample-benchmark/README.md` checked.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/016-script-subfolder-readmes/implementation-summary.md:65:Three parallel author streams (lane dirs, the model-benchmark scorer subtree, tests plus existing-README audit), each reading the real scripts for accuracy, then a verifier that confirmed coverage, template alignment, HVR, and key-file accuracy.
