.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:6:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:22:# Context Index — 121 deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:36:**Arc 1 — Build the model-benchmark mode (phases 001–007).** Generalize the one-off 120/003 benchmark rig into a first-class `model-benchmark` mode of the deep-agent-improvement skill: design the mode selector + 3 pluggable seams (001) -> MiniMax M2.7 deep-research of the build (002) -> build it (003) -> independent tri-model hardening review (007) and remediation of its findings (004) -> opt-in 5-dim scorer + SKILL docs (005) -> deep-loop empty-archive maintenance fix (006).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:38:**Arc 2 — Two co-equal lanes (phases 008–018).** Elevate model-benchmark from a "Mode 4" bolt-on to a lane co-equal with agent-improvement across every surface: command (008) -> SKILL.md (009) -> references/assets (010) -> agent note (011) -> catalog/playbook/advisor (012) -> scripts (013), then harden it with two independent deep-review -> remediation cycles — gpt-5.5 (014 -> 015) and Opus 4.8 (017 -> 018) — plus per-subfolder code READMEs (016).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:44:The tri-model hardening review of the Arc-1 build was originally scaffolded as a **separate packet, `122-session-120-121-deep-review`**, and run on 2026-05-28. Its findings were remediated the same day in `121/004`. On **2026-05-29** that review packet was **folded into 121** as phase `007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:51:Numbers are **not** reshuffled to "fix" this — the sequence is the provenance record, and the git history (`git log --follow`) traces every folder back through its `git mv` renames.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:55:## 3. Phase renames (2026-05-30 reorg)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:57:Four phase folders were renamed via `git mv` (history preserved) to satisfy the literal-naming rule (system-spec-kit Rule 20): remediation packets must take the form `NNN-fix-<source>-for-<target>`, and cryptic finding-code jargon is not allowed.
