.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-011.md:116:No active P0. After arbitration, the active P1 set is reduced to genuine correctness/security defects (dispatcher cwd propagation, cwd-check prefix escape, criteria command-execution surface, grader unbounded score). The headline "dispatcher + 5-dim scorer shipped-but-not-wired" finding is an **intended, spec-documented P2 deferral** (spec.md:166 §7), correctly downgraded. Remaining P1s are real but none is release-blocking by itself; they warrant fix-before-promote. Per the verdict matrix (no active P0, active P1 remains) the gate is CONDITIONAL.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-011.md:120:Capstone iteration (11 of 11) — loop converged. No next dimension. Remediation backlog for follow-up packet: (1) fix `cwd-check.cjs` prefix boundary; (2) forward `cwd` to all dispatch-model executors; (3) clamp grader score `[0,1]`; (4) decide trusted-author policy for criteria `execSync`; (5) re-verify promote-candidate.cjs:168 in scope; (6) wire mode metadata into reduce-state dashboard; (7) reconcile REQ-004 `--cwd` wording. Items 4–7 are P2 follow-ons.
