.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:1:deep-agent-improvement gained a first-class model-benchmark mode and, on top of it, became a genuine two-lane skill end to end: Lane A (improve an agent file) and Lane B (benchmark a model or prompt framework) are now co-equal at the command, doc, agent, and on-disk layers. The capability was built from a designed mode-selector + pluggable seams, then hardened by two independent deep-review -> remediation cycles (gpt-5.5 and Opus 4.8) before Lane B shipped.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:3:> Spec parent: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode` (covers the 121 program across both arcs — Build 001-007 and Two-lane 008-018; consolidated here by the 019 doc closeout).
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:9:### Arc 1 — Build the model-benchmark mode (phases 001-007)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:15:- **New `dispatch-model.cjs` generic dispatcher** runs a model against fixtures under prompt-framework variants — the Lane B equivalent of dispatching a Claude agent, but for arbitrary models across the 5 executors.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:23:- **SKILL.md documented the model-benchmark mode for the first time** (WHEN-TO-USE case + scorer options), with the README structure table refreshed for the new scripts and the `scorer/` subtree. DQI moved 94 -> 97 (excellent band). Regression tests cover both scorer paths plus unknown-scorer fallback.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:39:- **`/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` now resolves a use-case lane.** When an agent path is supplied it auto-resolves to Lane A and runs exactly as before (CMD-1 behavioral identity), so existing invocations are untouched. A `--lane=model-benchmark` flag or a `--profile` argument routes to Lane B, and a lane question appears only when the lane is genuinely ambiguous.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:40:- **New dedicated `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command** plus its gemini mirror and two Lane B workflow YAMLs (`deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) that run `loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark`, reduce, journal, and offer mode-aware promotion.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:46:- **The skill doc presents Lane A and Lane B as parallel sections** instead of modes 1 to 3 plus a trailing Mode 4. A WHEN TO USE two-lane table was added, and the smart router gained a `MODEL_BENCHMARK` intent at weight 5 with a matching RESOURCE_MAP entry. DQI stayed in the excellent band at 97.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:54:- **The `@deep-agent-improvement` awareness note went from "Mode awareness" to "Lane awareness"** across all 4 runtime mirrors, byte-identical (mirror-drift 0). The note makes clear there is one agent and Lane B dispatches models through `dispatch-model.cjs`, never a second Claude agent.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:72:- **Remediated all of them (phase 015):** the 1 P0 + 16 P1 + 16 P2 findings were closed before Lane B shipped.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:74:- **Remediated the Opus findings (phase 018):** the 4 P1 + 13 P2 were closed with one disposition each — including a materializer fixture-id guard, a bundle-gate criteria-exec gate, removal of dead Mode-4 anchors, and an executable Lane B benchmark-mode promotion path matched to its documented truth, with regression tests.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:80:This release covers the entire 121 program. Arc 1 designed (001), deep-researched (002), built (003), and hardened (007 review -> 004 remediation) the model-benchmark mode, then added the opt-in 5-dim scorer + docs (005) and a maintenance fix (006). Arc 2 elevated model-benchmark from a "Mode 4" bolt-on to a lane co-equal with agent-improvement across command (008), SKILL.md (009), references/assets (010), the agent note (011), catalog/playbook/advisor (012), and scripts (013), then hardened it with two independent deep-review -> remediation cycles — gpt-5.5 (014 -> 015) and Opus 4.8 (017 -> 018) — plus per-subfolder code READMEs (016). The tri-model hardening review of Arc 1 was originally scaffolded as separate packet 122 and folded into 121 as phase 007 on 2026-05-29; that is why remediation phase 004 carries a lower number than the review it remediates (007). Each phase ran as an agentic workflow with an independent verification pass.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:93:No migration required for callers of `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` with an agent path, which behave exactly as before. New work that benchmarks a model or prompt framework should use `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` or pass `--lane=model-benchmark`; opt into the 5-dim rubric with `--scorer=5dim` (default stays `pattern`). Internal scripts moved into lane subdirs, so any external caller hardcoding `scripts/<name>.cjs` should update to `scripts/<lane>/<name>.cjs`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/027-resume-continuation.md:16:This scenario validates that the current release uses standalone `new`-mode sessions, so continuation happens by archiving the previous run and starting a fresh `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` session.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/027-resume-continuation.md:23:- Real user request: `` Validate that the current release uses standalone `new`-mode sessions, so continuation happens by archiving the previous run and starting a fresh `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` session. ``
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/027-resume-continuation.md:45:| RT-027 | Fresh-Session Continuation After Archive | Validate Fresh-Session Continuation After Archive | `Validate that new-mode continuation archives the previous run and starts a fresh session.` | Step 1 -- Run the initial session (2 iterations):<br><br><br>/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop &quot;.opencode/agents/debug.md&quot; :confirm --spec-folder={spec} --iterations=2<br><br><br>Step 2 -- Archive the previous session folder:<br><br><br>ARCHIVE_ROOT=&quot;{spec}/improvement_archive/$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)&quot;<br>mkdir -p &quot;{spec}/improvement_archive&quot;<br>mv &quot;{spec}/improvement&quot; &quot;$ARCHIVE_ROOT&quot;<br><br><br>Step 3 -- Start a fresh session against the same target:<br><br><br>/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop &quot;.opencode/agents/debug.md&quot; :confirm --spec-folder={spec} --iterations=2<br><br><br>Verification:<br><br><br>ARCHIVE_ROOT=&quot;$(ls -dt {spec}/improvement_archive/* &#124; head -1)&quot;<br>test -d &quot;$ARCHIVE_ROOT&quot;<br><br><br>ARCHIVE_ROOT=&quot;$(ls -dt {spec}/improvement_archive/* &#124; head -1)&quot;<br>test -d &quot;$ARCHIVE_ROOT&quot;<br><br><br>ARCHIVE_ROOT=&quot;$(ls -dt {spec}/improvement_archive/* &#124; head -1)&quot;<br>test -d &quot;$ARCHIVE_ROOT&quot;<br><br><br>ARCHIVE_ROOT=&quot;$(ls -dt {spec}/improvement_archive/* &#124; head -1)&quot;<br>test -d &quot;$ARCHIVE_ROOT&quot;<br><br><br>node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/improvement-journal.cjs --read {spec}/improvement/improvement-journal.jsonl &#124; python3 -c &quot;<br>import sys, json<br>events = json.load(sys.stdin)<br>starts = [e for e in events if e[&#x27;eventType&#x27;] == &#x27;session_start&#x27;]<br>assert len(starts) &gt;= 1, f&#x27;Expected at least 1 session_start event in the fresh session, got {len(starts)}&#x27;<br>details = starts[0].get(&#x27;details&#x27;, {})<br>assert details.get(&#x27;lineageMode&#x27;, &#x27;new&#x27;) == &#x27;new&#x27;, f&quot;Expected lineageMode new, got {details.get(&#x27;lineageMode&#x27;)}&quot;<br>assert details.get(&#x27;generation&#x27;, 1) == 1, f&quot;Expected generation 1, got {details.get(&#x27;generation&#x27;)}&quot;<br>print(&#x27;PASS - fresh session starts in new mode after archive&#x27;)<br>&quot; | The archived `improvement/` directory is preserved under `improvement_archive/` before the next run begins; The fresh run creates a new `improvement/` directory instead of reusing the archived one; The fresh session starts in `new` mode with a new session id and generation `1`; Iteration numbering restarts from `1` in the fresh session journal; No unsupported lineage flags or multi-generation session behaviors are required or documented as shipped | `terminal transcript, command output, generated files, and PASS/FAIL verdict` | After archiving the prior runtime folder and starting a fresh session, the repository preserves the old evidence separately, the new session journal starts in `new` mode with generation `1`, and the fresh run begins again at iteration `1` without claiming unshipped continuation semantics. | If the archive step fails: verify the spec folder path is correct and `improvement/` exists before moving it<br>If the fresh run reuses the archived directory: inspect the init phase to confirm it always creates a new runtime folder<br>If lineage metadata is not `new` / generation `1`: compare the emitted `session_start` details against the current-release session model in `SKILL.md`<br>If docs still mention unsupported lineage flags or multi-generation continuation modes: remove the stale wording from the playbook and command examples |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/027-resume-continuation.md:74:| `../../SKILL.md` | Skill entry point and operator contract for deep-agent-improvement |
