.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:1:Initial release of `deep-agent-improvement` -- an evaluator-first skill for bounded agent improvement with 5-dimension integration-aware scoring, dynamic profiling, deterministic benchmarks, and guarded promotion. The skill evaluates any agent across its full system integration surface rather than just checking keyword presence in the markdown file. Developed across 8 phases under spec folder `041-sk-recursive-agent-loop`, originally as `sk-recursive-agent` and renamed in Phase 008. The goal is to make the workflow easier to follow and easier to trust.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:73:The `@agent-improver` agent and `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command are mirrored across all 5 runtimes (OpenCode, Claude, Codex, .agents, Gemini). The integration scanner checks mirror parity automatically.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:85:Renamed from `sk-recursive-agent` to `deep-agent-improvement` across 187+ files and 1129+ occurrences. Command moved from `/speckit:recursive-agent` to `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`. Agent renamed from `@recursive-agent` to `@agent-improver`. Zero stale references remaining (verified by fresh sub-agent audit).
