.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:91:Existing improvement sessions without the new runtime-truth fields continue to run unchanged (backward compatible). Operators invoking `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` now get a reviewable audit journal, mutation coverage graph, trade-off detection, and stability-aware promotion gates - all enforced orchestrator-side so the proposal-only agent constraint is preserved. Legacy `sk-agent-improver` paths are fully removed; update any external references to `deep-agent-improvement`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:97:> This release documented four lifecycle modes for re-entering an `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` session: `resume`, `restart`, `fork`, and `completed-continue`. None of the four were ever wired up. The command has no input for lineage mode, the reducer does not carry ancestry across sessions, and the journal helper has no multi-session boundary event. Every invocation is a fresh `new` session.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/028-legal-stop-gates.md:45:| RT-028 | Legal-Stop Gate Blocking | Validate Legal-Stop Gate Blocking | `Validate that failed legal-stop gates record blockedStop instead of converged.` | /deep:start-agent-improvement-loop &quot;.opencode/agents/debug.md&quot; :confirm --spec-folder={spec} --iterations=5<br><br><br>Verification:<br><br><br>node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/improvement-journal.cjs --read {spec}/improvement/improvement-journal.jsonl &#124; python3 -c &quot;<br>import sys, json<br>events = json.load(sys.stdin)<br># Check for legal_stop_evaluated events<br>lse = [e for e in events if e[&#x27;eventType&#x27;] == &#x27;legal_stop_evaluated&#x27;]<br>blocked = [e for e in events if e[&#x27;eventType&#x27;] == &#x27;blocked_stop&#x27;]<br>GATES = [&#x27;contractGate&#x27;, &#x27;behaviorGate&#x27;, &#x27;integrationGate&#x27;, &#x27;evidenceGate&#x27;, &#x27;improvementGate&#x27;]<br>if lse:<br>    gates = lse[-1].get(&#x27;details&#x27;, {}).get(&#x27;gateResults&#x27;, {})<br>    present = [g for g in GATES if g in gates]<br>    print(f&#x27;legal_stop_evaluated found - gates present: {present}&#x27;)<br>if blocked:<br>    failed = blocked[-1].get(&#x27;details&#x27;, {}).get(&#x27;failedGates&#x27;, [])<br>    print(f&#x27;blocked_stop found - failed gates: {failed}&#x27;)<br>    print(&#x27;PASS - blockedStop recorded with failed gate details&#x27;)<br>else:<br>    ends = [e for e in events if e[&#x27;eventType&#x27;] in (&#x27;session_ended&#x27;, &#x27;session_end&#x27;)]<br>    if ends and ends[-1].get(&#x27;details&#x27;, {}).get(&#x27;stopReason&#x27;) == &#x27;converged&#x27;:<br>        print(&#x27;INFO - session converged (all gates passed), no blockedStop expected&#x27;)<br>    else:<br>        print(&#x27;INFO - no blocked_stop event found; may need scenario with intentional gate failure&#x27;)<br>&quot; | `legal_stop_evaluated` event emitted with nested `details.gateResults` containing all 5 gate bundles; `contractGate`: structural >= 90 AND systemFitness >= 90; `behaviorGate`: ruleCoherence >= 85 AND outputQuality >= 85; `integrationGate`: integration >= 90 AND no drift ambiguity; `evidenceGate`: benchmark pass AND repeatability pass; `improvementGate`: weighted delta >= configured threshold; When any gate fails: `blocked_stop` event emitted with `failedGates[]` and `reason`; Session `stopReason` is `blockedStop` (not `converged`) when gates fail; The session continues iterating (does not prematurely terminate) when gates block convergence; If all 5 gates pass: `converged` stopReason is used instead | `terminal transcript, command output, generated files, and PASS/FAIL verdict` | When convergence math would trigger stop but at least one gate bundle fails, the journal contains a `blocked_stop` event with the failing gate names, and the session's `stopReason` is `blockedStop` -- the session does NOT claim `converged`. | If `legal_stop_evaluated` is missing: verify the orchestrator calls the legal-stop evaluation after convergence math triggers<br>If `blocked_stop` is missing when a gate fails: check the conditional that routes to `blocked_stop` vs `converged` based on gate results<br>If `stopReason` is `converged` despite failing gates: the gate-check-before-converge guard is bypassed; check the orchestrator&#x27;s stop-reason assignment logic<br>If gate results are empty: verify each gate bundle function is implemented and returns a pass/fail result |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/028-legal-stop-gates.md:74:| `../../SKILL.md` | Skill entry point and operator contract for deep-agent-improvement |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:1:This release lands the deep-agent-improvement portion of the packets 108 plus 110 auto-review uplift program. One reusable teaching from the upstream `dzianisv/opencode-plugins` auto-review package now applies to the mutation-coverage pipeline: a signature-based dedup that prevents the same mutation from being proposed twice across iterations of the same improvement arc. The signature is stored alongside each mutation in `mutation-coverage.json`. The council was explicit in section 10.6 that the authoritative storage IS `mutation-coverage.json`, NOT `agent-improvement-state.jsonl`, so the replay consumer and the coverage reducer share one source of truth. Every mechanism cleared a 5-of-5 unanimous deep-ai-council review by `cli-codex gpt-5.5 xhigh fast` before any code shipped.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:63:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/mutation-coverage.cjs` | New `computeMutationSignature(mutation)` function returning `sha256(dimension + ":" + mutationType + ":" + targetSection + ":" + normalized_body.slice(0,64))`. Pre-propose check against existing `mutations[]` signatures. Skipped proposals record `EXHAUSTED-FROM: iter-NNN`. Signatures stored on each entry in `mutation-coverage.json` (council section 10.6: authoritative storage is `mutation-coverage.json`, NOT `agent-improvement-state.jsonl`). Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:64:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Reducer updated to recognize the new `signature` field. Backward-compatible fallthrough when the field is absent. Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:70:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` | Documents the signature scheme, the `DEEP_AGENT_IMPROVEMENT_SKIP_DEDUP=1` env-var bypass, and the `EXHAUSTED-FROM:` skip-reason format. Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:71:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/034-replay-consumer.md` | New manual playbook scenario verifying that the replay consumer respects signature dedup. Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:2:title: "deep-agent-improvement: Prove an Agent Got Better Before You Ship It"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:5:  - "deep-agent-improvement"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:13:# deep-agent-improvement
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:23:Editing an agent prompt is usually guesswork. You reword a rule, the prompt reads better, you ship it, and you never know whether the agent got stronger or only different. `deep-agent-improvement` replaces that guess with measured evidence.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:35:| **Lane A — Agent-Improvement** | Improve a bounded agent `.md` file (the default; most of this README) | `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:36:| **Lane B — Model-Benchmark** | Benchmark a model or prompt framework against fixtures | `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:38:Lane B (the model-benchmark mode) is documented in `SKILL.md` §4 and `references/model-benchmark/`. To match the two lanes, `references/`, `assets/`, and `scripts/` are each split into `agent-improvement/`, `model-benchmark/`, and `shared/` subdirs.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:52:The `@deep-agent-improvement` agent (under `.opencode/agents/`) is the mutator that writes one candidate. This skill is the evaluator and the rulebook around it: it owns scoring, benchmarking, the promotion gates, and the stop logic. `sk-prompt` rewrites prompt prose on request. This skill decides whether a rewrite earned its place.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:84:/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop ".opencode/agents/debug.md" :confirm --spec-folder={spec_folder}
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:93:node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs --agent=debug
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:96:node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/generate-profile.cjs --agent=.opencode/agents/debug.md
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:99:node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/score-candidate.cjs --candidate=.opencode/agents/debug.md
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:113:- **Candidate generation.** Writes exactly one bounded candidate under `candidates/` without touching the canonical target. Generation is delegated to the `@deep-agent-improvement` agent, which reads the charter and manifest first and stops before scoring begins, which keeps the mutator and the evaluator independent.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:123:- **Surface discovery.** `scan-integration.cjs` inventories the canonical agent file, three runtime mirrors, the `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command markdown, YAML workflow assets, skill references, global docs, and the `system-skill-advisor` routing path. The score reflects the whole integration, not the prompt in isolation.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:125:- **Command dispatch.** Owns the path that turns the skill into a runnable loop. `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` collects setup inputs, picks `:auto` or `:confirm`, and points the operator at the matching YAML workflow, which is where the real agent dispatch and journal emission happen.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:167:.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:172:|   +-- model-benchmark/        # Lane B (3): evaluator contract, benchmark operator guide, mixed-executor
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:176:|   `-- model-benchmark/        # Lane B: benchmark fixtures + profiles
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:179:|   +-- model-benchmark/        # Lane B (2): run-benchmark, dispatch-model + scorer/ subtree
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:182:`-- manual_testing_playbook/    # 42 manual scenarios across 9 categories (09 = model-benchmark / Lane B)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:212:| `shared/loop-host.cjs` | Mode-switch entry point: routes to Lane A or `--mode=model-benchmark` (Lane B) |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:213:| `model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs` | Lane B: run a model against fixtures under prompt-framework variants |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:214:| `model-benchmark/scorer/**` | Lane B: ported decoupled scorer (deterministic checks + LLM grader harness) |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/README.md:261:The `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command and the `@deep-agent-improvement` agent are mirrored across runtimes. The integration scanner checks mirror parity on every run.
